Package: kalidasa
Title: Digital Archive for Sanskrit Analysis
Version: 0.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Mackenzie", "Haight", , "mackenzie.haight@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: kalidasa is a repository of the data from the Digital Corpus of Sanskrit (DCS). The DCS is a Sandhi-split corpus of Sanskrit texts with full morphological and lexical analysis designed for text-historical research in Sanskrit linguistics and philology. All data was scraped from the DCS, which is prepared by Oliver Hellwig and licensed under CC-BY 4.0.
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
